Peru Stocks: Cementos Lima, Credicorp, Luz del Sur, Siderperu

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-20T21:14:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/peru-stocks-el-brocal-candente-intergroup-minsur-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for the second day in three,
losing 1.1 percent to 18,798.67. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index
slid 0.4 percent to 2,559.53.  Industrial stocks, banks and utilities slumped on investor
concerns that weekend opinion polls will show ex-renegade army
Col. Ollanta Humala as the frontrunner for Peru’s June 5
presidential elections, said Jose Luis Bustamante, head of
trading at Cartisa SAB. Humala has pledged to renegotiate
contracts with foreign companies if he’s elected.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, plunged 6.3 percent to 74
cents, its lowest closing price since July 20.  Empresa
Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA,
Latin America’s largest steelmaker, fell 3.9 percent to 1.25
soles.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest
cement maker, dropped 3.2 percent to 2.40 soles.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial services
company, fell 2.9 percent to $90.40. Luz del Sur (LUSURC1 PE),
Peru’s largest electricity distributor, declined 2.8 percent to
5.25 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
